2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - **Gossamer**: Node.js/TypeScript tool that indexes Entire CLI checkpoint data from git branches and serves via HTTP+WebSocket API, with an Electron UI
   - **electron-vite**: Build tool for the Electron app (not Expo/React Native as memory incorrectly stated)
   - **concurrently**: npm package to run multiple commands simultaneously
   - **entire/checkpoints/v1 branch**: Git branch where `entire` CLI stores checkpoint data in a shard directory structure (`<2hex>/<10hex>/metadata.json`, `full.jsonl`, etc.)
   - **Shadow branches** (`entire/<hash>-<hash>`): In-progress session branches
   - **Git worktree**: `.gossamer/checkpoints` worktree checked out from `entire/checkpoints/v1`, used by gossamer indexer to read checkpoint files from the filesystem
   - **execSync blocking event loop**: Core bug — synchronous git operations blocked all HTTP requests
   - **refs/heads/ resolution**: Git ambiguity where bare branch name resolves to `origin/` tracking ref instead of local branch
   - **merge --ff-only risk**: Was inadvertently fast-forwarding local branch to origin (destructive when origin had bad commits)
   - **entire post-commit hook**: `entire hooks git post-commit` — creates checkpoint commit on `entire/checkpoints/v1`, pushes to remote; if push fails, reverts local branch
   - **diff-tree --numstat**: Git command to get per-file line addition/deletion stats for a commit
   - **CheckpointIdGitOidJoin**: Prisma table mapping checkpoint IDs to git commit OIDs (gitOid is @id, checkpointId has @@index)

